\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 42.         Convallaria}     L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By J. Ponert. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Glabrous, scapose, perennial herbs with a creeping, branched rhizome. Leaves arising from the rhizome, but with convolute, sheathing bases which simulate a leafy stem; each such stem consists of c. 5 scales and 1-4 foliage-leaves. Inflorescence racemose; pedicels usually deflexed. Flowers white or pink. Perianth more or less campanulate, the segments usually connate for about 2/3 of their length. Stamens usually 6; anthers attached near the base, introrse. Style simple. Fruit a berry.
