\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial, with creeping rhizome. Stems erect, with 2 scale leaves at the base and 2 foliage leaves near the apex. Leaves alternate. Inflorescence a terminal raceme. Flowers white; pedicels slender, articulated. Perianth of 4 free, patent segments. Stamens 4, shorter than perianth; anthers dorsifixed, introrse. Ovary 2-locular with 2 ovules in each loculus. Fruit a berry; seeds 1-3.
